# Pre-push capability matrix for Linux/amd64 -- the secondary LP64 target.
#
# Same matrix as Linux-aarch64; the TRUST differs.  The amd64 Dis JIT
# (comp-amd64.c) is present but UNVERIFIED under LP64, so JIT run-mode cells are
# `skip` (visible, never silently green) until vetted.  The interpreter and the
# pure-VM suites are the portable reference path and are expected to pass, so
# they stay `require` -- running the gate here is how amd64 stops being untested.
#
# See tests/check/platforms/Linux-aarch64.manifest for the column / CELL grammar.

# ---- build matrix ----
build  emu                require
build  emu-g              require    headless build the lp64/web suites run under
build  emu/release        require    release link-check: DISPTRCHECK off must still build
build  emu-wrt            todo       wince/wrt config unmaintained

# ---- test matrix ----
test   cunit              require
test   lp64/emu-g/interp  require    interpreter is the portable reference path
test   lp64/emu-g/jit     skip       comp-amd64.c unverified under LP64
test   web/emu-g/interp   require
test   jitperf            skip       needs a trusted JIT; revisit with lp64/.../jit

# ---- docs ----
doc    man-coverage       todo       every /dis cmd has a man/1 page; then per-flag usage
